    <note>Cheng(1) Xiang [3103] The family was stranded in Huangzhou, Huangpo county when his father died at an early age. He and his brothers were raised and educated by their uncle, probably Dao [15708]. They were relatively poor since they owned no real estate and through the influence of his lineage elder cousin, Cheng(1) Lin [118], Xiang received an initial appointment as Huangpo county sherrif (wei) at the same time that his brother, Fan [3101], and cousin, Yu(2) [3114], also received offices on the basis of Lin's achievments. Xiang's next office was Jizhou, Jian county sherrif and it was probably at this time that Peng(1)  Siyong [1401] betrothed his daughter to Cheng(1) Hao [3102]. When Xiang was prefect of Honan fu during the 1040's, Zhou(1) Dunyi [504] held a minor office and Xiang was impressed, Dunyi clearly knew the 'Way' (Dao), and ordered his sons, Hao and Yi [3105], to study with him. Cheng Yi, WJ, 8.1a-6a, 6a-8a (wife, born Hou, who married Xiang at age of 19). CBD, 4, 3006-7.</note>
